body: Yosief Ghebrehiwet explains why the Tunisian revolution cannot be replicated in Eritrea:"the wholesale eviction of the adult student population from the cities and the overall low development level of the nation make it impossible for the kind of uprising that we are witnessing in Tunisia to be emulated in Eritrea."

title: Eritrea: The Tunisian revolution cannot be replicated in Eritrea
